Perfect help page for example pattern
DISCLAIMER: any other strings you add will not be colorized

Usage: 
  awesometool [options] command [args]

Options:
  -h, --help string       Show this message and exit.
  -v, --version stuff     Display the version of AwesomeTool.
  -f, --file filename     Specify a custom file to store your to-do list. Default is "tasks.json".
  -c, --completed         Show completed tasks in the list.

Commands:
  add                     Add a new task to the to-do list.
  list                    Display the current to-do list.
  complete                Mark a task as completed.
  remove                  Remove a task from the list.
  clear                   Clear all completed tasks from the list.

Use "awesometool [command] --help" for more information about a command.
